                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.116/94.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Straus</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Straus states that he is gratified to inform the department that he has
                    secured a favorable decision from the Porte freeing all officially recognized
                    religious, charitable, and educational institutions from the restrictive law
                    governing associations; and that he has also obtained a favorable decision for
                    transferring property and constructing buildings for the girls’ college at
                    Constantinople. Mr. Straus adds that he has obtained favorable action concerning
                    a general firman for Beirut College and irade for constructing Robert College
                    buildings.</p>
            </div>
